ladder muscle contractility","Inhibits testosterone production","Reduces inflammation in the prostate gland","Reduces prostate size through hormonal effects","Relaxes smooth muscle in prostate and bladder neck"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ESelective alpha-1 blockers work primarily through \u003Cstrong\u003Erelaxation of smooth muscle in the prostate and bladder neck\u003C/strong\u003E, which effectively reduces urinary outlet resistance and improves symptoms of benign prostatic hyperplasia. Selective alpha-1 blockers like tamsulosin are particularly useful because they preferentially target receptors in the genitourinary tract, resulting in fewer cardiovascular side effects compared to non-selective alpha blockers.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnlike 5-alpha reductase inhibitors, which \u003Cstrong\u003Ereduce prostate size through hormonal effects\u003C/strong\u003E, these medications do not alter the prostate\u0027s size or structure. They also do not \u003Cstrong\u003Eincrease bladder muscle contractility\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003Einhibit testosterone production\u003C/strong\u003E, as their mechanism focuses solely on smooth muscle tone regulation. While some patients may experience prostate inflammation, these medications do not \u003Cstrong\u003Ereduce inflammation in the prostate gland\u003C/strong\u003E. \u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Selective alpha-1 adrenergic blockers relax smooth muscle in the prostate and bladder neck to improve urinary symptoms.","Selective alpha-1 blockers have minimal effect on vascular tone compared to non-selective alpha blockers.","Common selective alpha-1 blockers include tamsulosin, alfuzosin, and silodosin."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth 